cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SDQ 

The paper proposes a novel neural network model for music signal processing, which involves dimensionality transformations and vector product neurons. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as cs.SD (Sound), cs.SI (Signal Processing), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of neural networks implies that the paper could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the experimental results on the iKala dataset suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.SDQ (Sound and Music Computing).
